# Shell scripts must always use LF line endings. They run inside Linux
# containers, and a CRLF here corrupts the shebang (`#!/bin/sh\r`) so the
# kernel can't find the interpreter — the script fails with "not found"
# (exit 127). This bit us on Windows checkouts where an editor rewrote the
# entrypoint scripts as CRLF and Docker baked them into the frontend image,
# crash-looping the nginx container. Forcing eol=lf keeps every checkout safe.
*.sh text eol=lf

# General normalization: store text as LF in the repo, let Git decide the
# working-tree ending for everything else.
* text=auto
